Square $ABCD$ in the coordinate plane has vertices at the points $A(1,1), B(-1,1), C(-1,-1),$ and $D(1,-1).$ Consider the following five transformations:
$\quad\bullet\qquad$ $L,$ a rotation of $90^{\circ}$ counterclockwise around the origin;
$\quad\bullet\qquad$ $R,$ a rotation of $90^{\circ}$ clockwise around the origin;
$\quad\bullet\qquad$ $H,$ a reflection across the $x$-axis;
$\quad\bullet\qquad$ $V,$ a reflection across the $y$-axis;
$\quad\bullet\qquad$ $F,$ a reflection across the line $y=x$.
Each of these transformations maps the square onto itself, but the positions of the labeled vertices will change. Find how many sequences of $10$ transformations chosen from $\{L, R, H, V, F\}$ will send all of the labeled vertices back to their original positions.
$\textbf{(A)}\ 5^8 \qquad\textbf{(B)}\ 5^9 \qquad\textbf{(C)}\ 5^{10} \qquad\textbf{(D)}\ 5^{11} \qquad\textbf{(E)}\ 5^{12}$
